The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Maran buys 37% of SpiceJet
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Maran buys 37% of SpiceJet
                            
	New Delhi, June 12 (PTI): Media magnate Kalanithi Maran today entered into an agreement to acquire a 37.7 per cent stake in low-cost airline SpiceJet for an estimated Rs 750 crore, thus becoming its single largest stakeholder.        
	The stake has been acquired by Maran, chairman and managing director of Chennai-based Sun TV Network, in his individual capacity and through his aviation company KAL Airways.        
	The shares have been acquired from current SpiceJet promoters, American investor Wilbur Ross and his investment companies, and Kansagara family-promoted Royal Holding Services Ltd.        
	While the price at which the deal was struck could not be ascertained, sources said Maran bought the 37.7 per cent stake at a price of around Rs 48 per share, entailing a total payout of about Rs 750 crore.        
	According to sources, the mandatory open offer to acquire an additional 20 per cent stake in Spicejet will be around Rs 58 per share.        
	As on March 31 this year, public shareholding in SpiceJet stood at 87.15 per cent, including 34.28 per cent held by institutional investors from India and abroad.                                                                                                                                       
